item.dc:creator: @SirPali SirPali
item.description:
@SirPali wrote:

No. Hamachi is a peer-to-peer VPN device. You act as the server in some cases, and as the client in others.

And, it as actually a much less secure system than using your actuall INET IP, because sometimes your clients can access random files on your hard drive/network.

item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

SirPali:

Hehe not A Hamachi, THE Hamachi Hamachi is a program wich enables users to make a kind of network, wich people can join. A lot of servers use this program to let people join there server, because it is more safer then using your “real” ip, because hamachi makes a new one for you. Because of this you are more secure not to get hacked or something

No. Hamachi is a peer-to-peer VPN device. You act as the server in some cases, and as the client in others.

And, it as actually a much less secure system than using your actuall INET IP, because sometimes your clients can access random files on your hard drive/network.
